# Full AWS Deployment Guide — MERN To-Do App

## Architecture

| Service              | Instance      | Port  |
| -------------------- | ------------- | ----- |
| React Frontend       | EC2 #1        | 3000  |
| Node/Express Backend | EC2 #2        | 5000  |
| Database             | MongoDB Atlas | Cloud |

---

# PART 1 — Create GitHub Repository

Push project to GitHub.

Inside project root:

```bash id="u1w8qr"
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial MERN Todo App"
```

Create public repo on GitHub named:

```text id="j5m2lc"
todo-app
```

Connect repo:

```bash id="g8v4pk"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/todo-app.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

---

# PART 2 — Create MongoDB Atlas Database

Go to MongoDB Atlas.

## Create Cluster

* Free Tier
* AWS
* Region close to you

---

## Create Database User

Example:

| Field    | Value             |
| -------- | ----------------- |
| Username | todoUser          |
| Password | StrongPassword123 |

---

## Network Access

Add:

```text id="s4k9wn"
0.0.0.0/0
```

---

## Copy Connection String

Example:

```env id="m2v7qx"
mongodb+srv://todoUser:StrongPassword123@cluster0.abcde.mongodb.net/todoapp?retryWrites=true&w=majority
```

Save it.

---

# PART 3 — Create Backend EC2 Instance

Go to Amazon EC2.

## Launch Instance

| Setting  | Value        |
| -------- | ------------ |
| Name     | todo-backend |
| AMI      | Ubuntu       |
| Type     | t2.micro     |
| Key Pair | Create new   |
| Storage  | 8GB          |

---

## Security Group Rules

### Inbound Rules

| Type       | Port | Source    |
| ---------- | ---- | --------- |
| SSH        | 22   | My IP     |
| Custom TCP | 5000 | 0.0.0.0/0 |

Launch instance.

Copy:

```text id="n8q3rl"
Backend Public IP
```

---

# PART 4 — Create Frontend EC2 Instance

Launch another Ubuntu instance.

| Setting | Value         |
| ------- | ------------- |
| Name    | todo-frontend |
| AMI     | Ubuntu        |
| Type    | t2.micro      |

---

## Security Group Rules

| Type       | Port | Source    |
| ---------- | ---- | --------- |
| SSH        | 22   | My IP     |
| Custom TCP | 3000 | 0.0.0.0/0 |

Copy:

```text id="x1v6mk"
Frontend Public IP
```

---

# PART 5 — Connect to Backend EC2

From AWS browser terminal or SSH:

```bash id="r4t9yc"
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@BACKEND_PUBLIC_IP
```

---

# PART 6 — Backend Deployment

## Update Ubuntu

```bash id="k7m2qd"
sudo apt update
```

---

## Install Node.js, npm, Git

```bash id="w3v8pl"
sudo apt install nodejs npm git -y
```

Verify:

```bash id="c6r1tn"
node -v
npm -v
```

---

## Clone GitHub Repo

```bash id="q9y4xm"
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/todo-app.git
```

---

## Enter Backend Folder

```bash id="p2u7lk"
cd todo-app/backend
```

---

## Install Packages

```bash id="d5n8qr"
npm install
```

---

## Create `.env`

```bash id="b1m4tc"
nano .env
```

Paste:

```env id="f7w2xp"
MONGO_URI=YOUR_MONGODB_URI
PORT=5000
```

Save:

* CTRL + O
* ENTER
* CTRL + X

---

## Start Backend

```bash id="v8q3ln"
node server.js
```

Expected:

```bash id="t4r7pk"
MongoDB Connected
Server running on port 5000
```

---

## Test Backend

Browser:

```text id="j6v9wc"
http://BACKEND_PUBLIC_IP:5000/api/tasks
```

Expected:

```json id="y3k1md"
[]
```

