# PART 8 — Frontend Deployment

## Update Ubuntu

```bash id="m9v2pk"
sudo apt update
```

---

## Install Node.js, npm, Git

```bash id="h4w7lc"
sudo apt install nodejs npm git -y
```

---

## Clone Repo

```bash id="r1n5qd"
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/todo-app.git
```

---

## Enter Frontend Folder

```bash id="c8u3tm"
cd todo-app/frontend
```

---

## Install Packages

npm install
```

---

## Create `.env`

```bash id="g7m1lr"
nano .env
```

Paste backend IP:

```env id="t5r8wc"
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://BACKEND_PUBLIC_IP:5000
```

Example:

```env id="j9k4qn"
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://13.233.xx.xx:5000
```

Save:

* CTRL + O
* ENTER
* CTRL + X

---

## Start Frontend

```bash id="w6p2xm"
npm start
```

---

# PART 9 — Open Website

Open:

```text id="n3v7ql"
http://FRONTEND_PUBLIC_IP:3000
```

Your MERN To-Do App should work live.

